{"schema_version":"1.7.3","id":"USN-2941-1","published":"2016-03-24T12:51:55.229076Z","modified":"2025-10-13T04:34:13Z","related":["UBUNTU-CVE-2013-2236","UBUNTU-CVE-2016-2342"],"upstream":["CVE-2013-2236","CVE-2016-2342","UBUNTU-CVE-2013-2236","UBUNTU-CVE-2016-2342"],"summary":"quagga vulnerabilities","details":"Kostya Kortchinsky discovered that Quagga incorrectly handled certain route\ndata when configured with BGP peers enabled for VPNv4. A remote attacker\ncould use this issue to cause Quagga to crash, resulting in a denial of\nservice, or possibly execute arbitrary code. (CVE-2016-2342)\n\nIt was discovered that Quagga incorrectly handled messages with a large\nLSA when used in certain configurations. A remote attacker could use this\nissue to cause Quagga to crash, resulting in a denial of service. This\nissue only affected Ubuntu 12.04 LTS. (CVE-2013-2236)\n","affected":[{"package":{"name":"quagga","ecosystem":"Ubuntu:14.04:LTS","purl":"pkg:deb/ubuntu/quagga@0.99.22.4-3ubuntu1.1?arch=source&distro=trusty"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0"},{"fixed":"0.99.22.4-3ubuntu1.1"}]}],"versions":["0.99.22.1-2","0.99.22.4-1","0.99.22.4-2","0.99.22.4-3","0.99.22.4-3ubuntu1"],"ecosystem_specific":{"availability":"No subscription required","binaries":[{"binary_name":"quagga","binary_version":"0.99.22.4-3ubuntu1.1"}]},"database_specific":{"cves_map":{"cves":[{"id":"CVE-2016-2342","severity":[{"score":"CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:H/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H","type":"CVSS_V3"},{"score":"high","type":"Ubuntu"}]}],"ecosystem":"Ubuntu:14.04:LTS"},"source":"https://github.com/canonical/ubuntu-security-notices/blob/main/osv/usn/USN-2941-1.json"}}],"references":[{"type":"ADVISORY","url":"https://ubuntu.com/security/notices/USN-2941-1"},{"type":"REPORT","url":"https://ubuntu.com/security/CVE-2013-2236"},{"type":"REPORT","url":"https://ubuntu.com/security/CVE-2016-2342"}]}